Pakistan thumped England by 127 runs in the third and final test to take the series and with it rose to No2 in the rankings, leaving England at sixth.Pakistan won the second test in Dubai by 178 runs and the first test ended in a draw in Abu Dhabi.Asked about his reaction to the defeat, Bayliss replied: "It's obviously one of disappointment. The players, as well, at the moment are very disappointed - obviously knowing we had a chance to win probably three matches here."We were in all three with a chance of winning, but in the end we weren't quite good enough."In the first test, bad light ended play with the tourists needing 25 runs.